Buccal mass and radula
.

The muscular portion of the buccal mass ~ 2/3 the size of the oral tube length (Fig. 
5a
). The chitinous labial cuticle found at the anterior end of the muscular portion of the buccal mass bears bifurcated and short jaw rodlets (Fig. 
7a, b
). The radular formula of CASIZ 228939 is 37 
x
19.1.19 (Fig. 
7c
). The rachidian tooth is triangular and short. The inner and outer surfaces of the inner lateral teeth have three denticles on each side of the central cusp (Fig. 
7d
). The central cusp on the inner lateral tooth is ~ 2
x
the length of the adjacent denticles. The middle lateral teeth have a short central cusp with three or four denticles (Fig. 
7e
). The outer lateral teeth have a rounded main cusp with three or four denticles (Fig. 
7f
).
